<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="253" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,341,906]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicName box="[199,376,629,653]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recisa">
<emphasis box="[199,376,629,653]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">Anthaxia recisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erroneously synonymised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily" box="[764,1007,629,654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" refString="Bily, S. &amp; Kuban, V. (2010) A revision of the Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) melancholica and A. (H.) thunbergi species-groups (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Buprestinae: Anthaxiini). Folia Heyrovskyana, series A, 18 (1 - 3), 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="2010">
Bílý &amp; Kubáň (
<number box="[940,999,630,654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gory &amp; Laporte, 1839" authorityName="Gory &amp; Laporte" authorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thunbergi" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[1071,1172,629,653]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1189,1209,630,653]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">H</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1234,1342,629,653]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">thunbergi</emphasis>
Gory &amp; Laporte, 
<number box="[253,313,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" value="1839.0">1839</number>
</taxonomicName>
; this act was based only on the description and the poor illustration of 
<bibRefCitation author="Thery" box="[1126,1279,665,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" refString="Thery, A. (1947) Buprestides d'Angola. Arquivos do Museo Bocage, 18, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1947">
Théry (
<number box="[1210,1271,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" value="1947.0">1947</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. After having studied the 
<typeStatus box="[282,380,701,726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[418,510,702,725]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recisa">
<emphasis box="[418,510,702,725]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">A.recisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and comparing it with the 
<typeStatus box="[816,919,701,726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1096,701,725]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sjoestedti">
<emphasis box="[958,1096,701,725]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">A. sjoestedti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I failed to find any difference and I propose that 
<taxonomicName authority="Thery, 1947" authorityName="Thery" authorityYear="1947" box="[373,700,737,762]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recisa">
<emphasis box="[373,551,737,761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">Anthaxia recisa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thery" box="[562,700,737,762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" refString="Thery, A. (1947) Buprestides d'Angola. Arquivos do Museo Bocage, 18, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1947">
Théry, 
<number box="[644,700,738,762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" value="1947.0">1947</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kerremans, 1908" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1908" box="[938,1362,737,762]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sjoestedti">
<emphasis box="[938,1156,737,761]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">Anthaxia sjoestedti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kerremans" box="[1166,1362,738,762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" refString="Kerremans, C. (1908) 6. Buprestidae. In: Schultze, L. (Ed.), Forschungsreise im westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1903 - 1905. Bd. 1, Lfg. 1. Denkschriften der Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, Band XIII. pp. 133 - 136." type="journal article" year="1908">
Kerremans, 
<number box="[1306,1362,738,762]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and a junior synonym. In this way I have to correct the incorrect synonymy by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily" box="[963,1202,773,798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" refString="Bily, S. &amp; Kuban, V. (2010) A revision of the Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) melancholica and A. (H.) thunbergi species-groups (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Buprestinae: Anthaxiini). Folia Heyrovskyana, series A, 18 (1 - 3), 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="2010">
Bílý &amp; Kubáň (
<number box="[1135,1194,774,798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and I must stress the fact that the any proposed synonyms should be based on the study of the 
<typeStatus box="[972,1020,810,834]" pageId="7" pageNumber="253">type</typeStatus>
specimen (if it is accessible) and not only on the description.
</paragraph>
